#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.30:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Pañcaṅgikavagga "
msgstr "3. With Five Factors "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Nāgitasutta "
msgstr "30. With Nāgita "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.30:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "an5.30:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kosalesu cārikaṃ caramāno mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ yena icchānaṅgalaṃ nāma kosalānaṃ brāhmaṇagāmo tadavasari. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was wandering in the land of the Kosalans together with a large Saṅgha of mendicants when he arrived at a village of the Kosalan brahmins named Icchānaṅgala. "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "He stayed in a forest near Icchānaṅgala. "

# NOTE: Not sure why BB switches to “brahmin householders” here. Previously in AN he’s translated brāhmaṇagahapatika as “brahmins and householders”, as the contexts imply.
#. VAR: icchānaṅgalakā → icchānaṅgalikā (si)
msgctxt "an5.30:1.4"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho icchānaṅgalakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā: "
msgstr "The brahmins and householders of Icchānaṅgala heard: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:1.5"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu bho gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito icchānaṅgalaṃ anuppatto; icchānaṅgale viharati icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "“It seems the ascetic Gotama—a Sakyan, gone forth from a Sakyan family—has arrived at Icchānaṅgala. He is staying in a forest near Icchānaṅgala. "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.6"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato: "
msgstr "He has this good reputation: "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.7"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi, satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti’. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.8"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.9"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "an5.30:1.10"
msgid "Sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti. "
msgstr "It’s good to see such perfected ones.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho icchānaṅgalakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā tassā rattiyā accayena pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ ādāya yena icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bahidvārakoṭṭhake aṭṭhaṃsu uccāsaddamahāsaddā. "
msgstr "Then, when the night had passed, they took many different foods and went to the forest near Icchānaṅgala, where they stood outside the gates making a dreadful racket. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.31, sc2
msgctxt "an5.30:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nāgito bhagavato upaṭṭhāko hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time Venerable Nāgita was the Buddha’s attendant. "

msgctxt "an5.30:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ nāgitaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Nāgita, "

# NOTE: Thanks to the wonders of Youtube, we can hear just what that sounds like: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gFkmIxceFtQ
msgctxt "an5.30:2.3"
msgid "“ke pana kho, nāgita, uccāsaddamahāsaddā, kevaṭṭā maññe macchavilope”ti? "
msgstr "“Nāgita, who’s making that dreadful racket? You’d think it was fishermen hauling in a catch!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:2.4"
msgid "“Ete, bhante, icchānaṅgalakā brāhmaṇagahapatikā pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ ādāya bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhitā bhagavantaññeva uddissa bhikkhusaṃghañcā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, it’s these brahmins and householders of Icchānaṅgala. They’ve brought many different foods, and they’re standing outside the gates wanting to offer it specially to the Buddha and the mendicant Saṅgha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:2.5"
msgid "“Māhaṃ, nāgita, yasena samāgamaṃ, mā ca mayā yaso. "
msgstr "“Nāgita, may I never become famous. May fame not come to me. "

msgctxt "an5.30:2.6"
msgid "Yo kho, nāgita, nayimassa nekkhammasukhassa pavivekasukhassa upasamasukhassa sambodhasukhassa nikāmalābhī assa akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, yassāhaṃ nekkhammasukhassa pavivekasukhassa upasamasukhassa sambodhasukhassa nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī. "
msgstr "There are those who can’t get the bliss of renunciation, the bliss of seclusion, the bliss of peace, the bliss of awakening when they want, without trouble or difficulty like I can. "

#. VAR: taṃ → so (s1-3, km) | sohaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an5.30:2.7"
msgid "So taṃ mīḷhasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ lābhasakkārasilokasukhaṃ sādiyeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "Let them enjoy the filthy, lazy pleasure of possessions, honor, and popularity.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.30:3.1"
msgid "“Adhivāsetu dāni, bhante, bhagavā, adhivāsetu sugato; "
msgstr "“Sir, may the Blessed One please relent now! May the Holy One relent! "

msgctxt "an5.30:3.2"
msgid "adhivāsanakālo dāni, bhante, bhagavato. "
msgstr "Now is the time for the Buddha to relent. "

# NOTE: cp. AN 4.70, etc.
msgctxt "an5.30:3.3"
msgid "Yena yeneva dāni bhagavā gamissati taṃninnāva gamissanti brāhmaṇagahapatikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca. "
msgstr "Wherever the Buddha now goes, the brahmins and householders will incline the same way, as will the people of town and country. "

msgctxt "an5.30:3.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, thullaphusitake deve vassante yathāninnaṃ udakāni pavattanti; "
msgstr "It’s like when it rains heavily and the water flows downhill. "

msgctxt "an5.30:3.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhante, yena yeneva dāni bhagavā gamissati, taṃninnāva gamissanti brāhmaṇagahapatikā negamā ceva jānapadā ca. "
msgstr "In the same way, wherever the Buddha now goes, the brahmins and householders will incline the same way, as will the people of town and country. "

msgctxt "an5.30:3.6"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an5.30:3.7"
msgid "Tathā hi, bhante, bhagavato sīlapaññāṇan”ti. "
msgstr "Because of the Buddha’s ethics and wisdom.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.32, sc4
msgctxt "an5.30:4.1"
msgid "“Māhaṃ, nāgita, yasena samāgamaṃ, mā ca mayā yaso. "
msgstr "“Nāgita, may I never become famous. May fame not come to me. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.2"
msgid "Yo kho, nāgita, nayimassa nekkhammasukhassa pavivekasukhassa upasamasukhassa sambodhasukhassa nikāmalābhī assa akicchalābhī akasiralābhī, yassāhaṃ nekkhammasukhassa pavivekasukhassa upasamasukhassa sambodhasukhassa nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī. "
msgstr "There are those who can’t get the bliss of renunciation, the bliss of seclusion, the bliss of peace, the bliss of awakening when they want, without trouble or difficulty like I can. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.3"
msgid "So taṃ mīḷhasukhaṃ middhasukhaṃ lābhasakkārasilokasukhaṃ sādiyeyya. "
msgstr "Let them enjoy the filthy, lazy pleasure of possessions, honor, and popularity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:4.4"
msgid "Asitapītakhāyitasāyitassa kho, nāgita, uccārapassāvo—"
msgstr "What you eat, drink, chew, and taste ends up as excrement and urine. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.5"
msgid "eso tassa nissando. "
msgstr "This is its outcome. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:4.6"
msgid "Piyānaṃ kho, nāgita, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā—"
msgstr "When loved ones decay and perish, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress arise. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.7"
msgid "eso tassa nissando. "
msgstr "This is its outcome. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pāṭikulyatā → pāṭikkūlyatā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | paṭikkūlaytā (si)
msgctxt "an5.30:4.8"
msgid "Asubhanimittānuyogaṃ anuyuttassa kho, nāgita, subhanimitte pāṭikulyatā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "When you pursue meditation on the feature of ugliness, revulsion at the feature of beauty becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.9"
msgid "eso tassa nissando. "
msgstr "This is its outcome. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:4.10"
msgid "Chasu kho, nāgita, phassāyatanesu aniccānupassino viharato phasse pāṭikulyatā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "When you meditate observing impermanence in the six fields of contact, revulsion at contact becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.11"
msgid "eso tassa nissando. "
msgstr "This is its outcome. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.30:4.12"
msgid "Pañcasu kho, nāgita, upādānakkhandhesu udayabbayānupassino viharato upādāne pāṭikulyatā saṇṭhāti—"
msgstr "When you meditate observing rise and fall in the five grasping aggregates, revulsion at grasping becomes stabilized. "

msgctxt "an5.30:4.13"
msgid "eso tassa nissando”ti. "
msgstr "This is its outcome.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.30:4.14"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.30:4.15"
msgid "Pañcaṅgikavaggo tatiyo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.30:5.1"
msgid "Dve agāravupakkilesā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.30:5.2"
msgid "Dussīlānuggahitena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.30:5.3"
msgid "Vimuttisamādhipañcaṅgikā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an5.30:5.4"
msgid "Caṅkamaṃ nāgitena cāti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
